File: Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi. JOHANNESBURG - Panyaza Lesufi has been reappointed Gauteng MEC for Education. Earlier this week Lesufi was announced as the new Finance and e-Government MEC. In a statement, Gauteng Premier David Makhura said that he has taken the decision to place Lesufi back in his position as Gauteng Education and Youth Development MEC after careful consideration. READ: Lesufi's new role an upward demotion: Analyst "Yesterday (Thursday), I indicated that I was giving serious consideration to the request and would announce my decision soon. The decision to appoint each MEC to a specific portfolio was not taken lightly." "Accordingly, I have now decided that MEC Panyaza Lesufi will return to the Education portfolio as the MEC for Education and Youth Development.", read the statement. Nomantu Nkomo-Ralehoko, formerly Education MEC, will now head the Finance and e-Government portfolio. 